seal               : Atari's last console was marketed as the first '64-bit' system, but inside was a tangle of chips that almost nobody could program well: two powerful custom processors ('Tom' and 'Jerry') alongside an old 68000 that developers leaned on out of habit — strangling the very power Atari was advertising.
